
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append nodes to the result of a [data.connect] operation. It retrieves the [limit] and [offset] arguments from the [.arguments] node using [get-nodes], which are then added to the [data.read] operation to facilitate pagination. This allows for controlling the number of records returned and the starting point in the dataset.
add:x:@data.connect/*/data.read
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/limit
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/offset
